reviewText: Survivor Series is usually the biggest of the fall PPV's and this year does not disappoint.Six Man Table Match: Jehh Hardy, Bubba Ray Dudley and Spike Dudley vs. Three Minute Warning and Rico- Jeff Hardy and Bubba Ray Dudley fought in a Tag Team Tables match at Royal Rumble 2000 in the same arena Madison Square Garden and man what a match that was. Now they're teaming up with Spike to take on Bischoff's wrecking crew in Three Minute Warning and Rico. A fast paced match with some nice spots and even some throwback spots to the Royal Rumble 2000 match. Capped off by the reunnion of the Dudley Boyz. This match was an awesome opener. 9 out of 10 stars.Billy Kidman and Jamie Knoble for the Cruiserweight Championship- THe only bad thing about this match is that lately the only time the WWE Cruiserweight Championship is on PPV is when it's going to change hands. A solid and fast paced match that shows the perks of the Cruiserweight Division. 8 out of 10 stars.Victoria vs Trish Stratus in a Hardcore Match for the Women's Championship- A solid and hard hitting women's match that shows that the divas can do more than just look good. 7 out of 10.The Big Show vs Brock Lesnar w/Paul Heyman for the WWE Heavyweight Championship- The biggest wrestler in the WWE meets the strongest wrestler in the WWE. A solid and entertaining match that was kept short to avoid showing the Big Show's weaknesses. Features the annual Survivor Series screw job and was a nice kick off to a feud that the WWE would force feed us to death.Edge and Rey Mysterio vs Kurt Angle and Chris Benoit vs Los Guererros in a Triple Threat for the WWE Tag Team Championship- A solid match that drags in a couple of parts. Not as good as the Finals of the Tag Team tournament at No Mercy, but still a heck of a tag match that is a throwback to the glory days of the tag team division in the olf WWF. 8 out of 10 stars.Scott Steiner's WWE Debut- Chris Nowinski from RAW and Matt Hardy v.1 from Smackdown get thrown around by Big Poppa Pump in a debut that really got everyone pumpped for Steiner's ring return. An entertaing segment in the show and a worthy Return/Debut. 8 out of 10.Elimination Chamber:Booker T vs Chris Jericho vs Kane vs Rob Van Dam vs Shawn Michaels vs Triple H for the World Heavyweight Championship- This was the debut of the Elimination Chamber and what a debut it was. A brutal match with some very cool spots and an ending that was unexpected it's just too bad it was short lived. Eric Bischoff's brain child lived up to it's hype. 10 out of 10 stars.Survivor Series was an outstanding ppv. The smaller card gave each match time to do it's work and tell it's story. A couple extras on the dvd make this a must own for any WWE fans.

reviewText: Survivor Series 2002 is an absolutely historic PPV that is fondly remembered by wrestling fans, and with good reason. On this day in November of 2002, the WWE debuted their answer to WCW's phenomenal War Games concept- the Elimination Chamber. The gimmick match was an interesting concept, and was thankfully executed to perfection by the six men in the main event. In my opinion, there has never been an Elimination Chamber match as good as this one.1. Jeff Hardy, Bubba Ray Dudley, and Spike Dudley VS 3-Minute Warning, and Rico- A messy, sloppy, yet wild tables match. I personally didn't enjoy it too much, however if you are a fan of the gimmick, you might have. The crowd really got in to it, however, so it did it's job. ***2. Jamie Noble VS Billy Kidman- The best of the cruiserweight division from 2002 WWE, which isn't saying much. However, to their credit, they did put on a stellar match. Not the best I've seen from either guy (especially Noble- check out his stuff in ROH as James Gibson) but it was still very solid. An enjoyable filler match. **3/43. Victoria VS Trish Stratus- Mildly decent. *1/24. The Big Show VS Brock Lesnar- Without a doubt, the disappointment of the night. Coming off a marvelous fued with the Undertaker, Brock had tons of momentum, and yet they kill it by having him lose to the Big Show in less than five minutes. Absolute garbage. 1/2*5. Los Guerreros VS Edge and Rey Mysterio, Jr. VS Kurt Angle and Chris Benoit- A truly masterful match. This goes to show you how amazing the tag team division in Smackdown was at around this time. It was absolutely awesome...all three teams gave it their all. If it weren't for the main event, this would have easily been match of the night. ****1/26. The Elimination Chamber Match- Triple H VS Shawn Michaels VS Booker T VS Kane VS Rob Van Dam VS Chris Jericho- Let's break down each guy here;Kane- Boy, do I miss the old Kane. This was when he was actually looking like a true monster.Chris Jericho- Jericho was at the top of his game here. Absolutely hilarious throughout the entire match. Extremely entertaining.Booker T- Very entertaining style about him. He was booked very well around this time.Rob Van Dam- One of the most underrated guys of all time. Had tons of charisma, and an extremely entertaining, unorthodox style to him. In my mind, he should have been champion in 2002.Shawn Michaels- Just coming off an incredible return here.Triple H- A very good heel champion at this point.Put them all together, and you have a truly marvelous match. It was brutal, bloody, and lived up to all expectations. Phenomenal selling by all six guys, too. Great storytelling, and booking, as well. A truly great match- one of my favorite gimmick matches of all time. ****3/4Overall- This was, as I've said before, a very memorable PPV. It had an absolutely amazing double main event, an above average opener, and a solid undercard. The only absolute garbage of the night was a match that was less than five minutes long. A recommended PPV.8.5/10
summary: A Historic PPV, To Say the Least!

reviewText: I wanted to give this PPV five stars.  Aside from one match, it was really great and it looks like the superstars did their best in their respective matches.  But the Elimination Chamber was really just a disappointment.  It was so heavily hyped, the cover of the DVD and the Case were pictures of Elimination Chambers, the DVD menus, promos playing all throughout the entire event, you'd think this were a Hell in a Cell made of barbed wire with a flaming ceiling and broken glass super-glued to the walls.Anyway, we'll get to that later...Six Man Tag Team Elimination Table MatchThe Dudley Boyz (Buh Buh Ray and Spike) and Jeff Hardy vs Three Minute Warning (Jamal (or Umaga nowadays) and Rosie) and RicoIn my opinion, this was one of the best matches of the night, if not the best.  The action was palpable, and it was full of amazing bumps and high points.  Towards the end, D-Von returns (as him and Buh Buh Ray were separated due to that awful brand split) and they give Rico a 3D through a table to win.  Great match and plenty violent, though not ECW violent.  (9/10)WWE Cruiserweight ChampionshipBilly Kidman vs Jamie Noble (C)This was an average match, but still very solidly done.  The action was something sorely missing in WWE nowadays.  It was great, not one of the best, but a good show.  (7/10)WWE Women's ChampionshipTrish Stratus (C) vs VictoriaThe women's division in the WWE has a notorious reputation for being little more than eye candy with catfighting and two or three wrestling moves.  The last real women wrestlers, the likes of the Fabulous Moolah, Mae Young, Chyna, etc, are long gone, an replaced with "divas".  Trish Stratus and Victoria completely broke that diva image, if for one night, and put on a hardcore match that was unbelievable.  By normal standards, the match was not near the standards of a hardcore match the likes of Rob Van Dam and Jeff Hardy at Invasion, but just seeing the Women's Division rise above a joke in [...], and see blood drawn (and not from blading) makes this match a rare gem I'd like to see more of.  (8/10)WWE ChampionshipBrock Lesnar (C) vs The Big ShowJeez... this was a joke match.  I can't think of any other name for it but a joke match.  Lasts probably less than five minutes, this consists of Brock Lesnar selling The Big Show's super-heavy weight for a while, before finally starting to lift him up and do moves on him.  Paul Heyman turns on Lesnar and sides with The Big Show, who then wins the championship.  I don't know if they were afraid to put on a great match because of the hype of the Elimination Chamber, but this match was just a joke.  (0/10)WWE Tag Team Championship EliminationKurt Angle and Chris Benoit vs Edge and Rey Mysterio vs Los GuerrerrosAn impressive tag team match.  My only gripe was that it didn't bother to do a three-way tag match with three men in the ring at once, but having two men in the ring, who could then tag whoever the hell they wanted into the ring at any time.  The Guerrerros took advantage of this in a great way, but otherwise it was a sort of unnecessary stipulation.  Any match putting Rey Mysterio, Chris Benoit, Eddie Guerrerro, and Kurt Angle in the ring at once is bound to be a winner.  (8/10)Just a note:  Scott Steiner takes steroids.  How can anyone think he doesn't?World Heavyweight Championship  Elimination ChamberKane vs Rob Van Dam vs Chris Jericho vs Booker T vs Triple H (C) vs Shawn Michaels*sigh* as I mentioned above, this match was so hyped up, it could have been the only match on the pay per view.  Not like they bothered to really advertise much else save for some promos before the matches.Putting it short, the Elimination Chamber is NOT more brutal than the Hell in a Cell.The design of the Elimination Chamber is such that it encompasses the entire ring in a circular design.  A metal platform surrounding the ring covers up the mat and prevents the use of weapons.  The door is locked so a superstar can't get weapons or climb to the top of the Chamber, though because of the design, there'd really be no point.  Unlike the Hell in a Cell, which is a sturdy structure made of that nasty metal they use to make steel fences out of, the Chamber is made of heavy chains, which are not at all dangerous to flesh unless you hit someone really hard with a strip of it, though many pieces criss-crossing are about as dangerous as laying down on a bed of nails---which if you know your physics, isn't as dangerous as magicians make it look.  And also since the chains are painted black, that adds a soft layer to the metal.The roof is too stiff and held up by giant wires for any fighting to even want to take place upon.  I'm thinking if they broke through the roof, they could risk destroying the entire Chamber, and seriously endangering one or all of the superstars.  I can understand this being the first ever Elimination Chamber not wanting to risk such a thing, but that didn't really seem to make a difference.The method of fighting is something almost clever---there are glass chambers on four sides of the ring, in which four superstars wait five minutes before being randomly selected to enter, while two superstars start out.  Superstars need to be pinned or submit to be eliminated.Rob Van Dam was really the star of this match.  He's always one of a kind, and watching the sort of things he does border on the hilarious (not in a mocking way) and the awesome.  Seeing Jericho reach up from his chamber to grab Rob's leg as he climbs atop it is an example of such hilarity.  It's a shame that Rob is eliminated towards the middle.The one problem I had most with this match was that the superstars were overselling each other's moves and overselling the effects of the Chamber.  Within three minutes or so, Van Dam has slammed Triple H's face against the chains, and the camera lets you see Triple H's sparkling clean, unbruised, normal-colored face as he drops to the floor.  Next time he's up, he's mysteriously bleeding.  Seeing him blade so early is really disappointing, and if HHH botched it in any way and started bleeding profusely, end of match for him.By overselling opponents moves, I don't mean superstars get punched, then keel over and start bleeding or whatever.  I mean there is a point where Shawn Michaels comes in fresh, is given a clothesline, and tossed out of the ring, and is suddenly crawling about the outside acting as if he'd been in the match half an hour.  Jericho, likewise, appears exhausted quickly, with momentary spurts where he looks fresh again.  Triple H just looks like a mess... he hardly does many moves other than two DDTs, some running knee lifts, and some countered Pedigrees.  Other than that, he stumbles about exhaustedly, lays in a corner for a whole five or six minutes, and just sort of hobbles about with blood on his face.The match wasn't any show of athleticism.  It seemed to just be a sale of "look how brutal this Chamber is" and little more.  Luckily there was Rob Van Dam and Chris Jericho and even Booker T to put some fierce effort into it, and some amazing spectacles by RVD, including missing a turnbuckle jump, and clinging to the wall of the chamber, to then jump on Jericho, and the Five Star Frog Splash from atop one of the chambers.All in all, this was a sub-par match, perhaps at the brutality level of the average steel cage match or table match.  If it weren't for its long length, it would have been the sort of match you'd see on the average episode of RAW or Smackdown.  If it weren't for the extreme hype put around this match, I would have at least thought it an okay match, but it was an extreme disappointment.  Thankfully they still have Hell in a Cell matches.  (2/10)All in all, it's probably worth seeing, but the hype behind the Elimination Chamber really ruins the rest of the event.  Survivor Series becomes so obsessed with it that every other match no longer really matters.
summary: A solid PPV, but the hype of the Elimination Chamber led to disappointment

reviewText: I bought this for DVD and it is one of the best of 2002.  Here are the matches:Six Man Table Match - Jeff Hardy, Buh Buh and Spike vs 3-Minute Warning and Rico.  This match had amazing ways of putting ppl thru tables.  But the biggest shock of the night was D-von coming to his brother's rescue to help him win the match and the Dudleyz reuniting!  ***1/2 (outta *****)Cruiserweight title match - Noble vs Kidman.  I aint big on these kinds of matches, but these guys were incredible.  The moves were great, stuff i've never seen before.  Kidman pulls off the win with the Shooting Star Press.  ****Women's title hardcore match - Trish vs Victoria.  Believe it or not, this was pretty good.  I've seen better hardcore matches, but i expected this to be worse, and i was wrong.  Victoria wins after a snap suplex, which is kinda weak.  **Triple-Threat Elimination WWE Tag Team Titles match:  Edge & Mysterio vs Angle and Benoit vs Los Guerreros.  This was probably the 2nd best match of the night.  Despite the Guerreros winning, this had some great spots in it, and all the teams gave it their all in this match.  *****Steiner makes his debut and beats up Mattitude and Nowinski, but that wasnt a match.Undisputed title - Brock Lesner vs The Big Show.  This was an ok match, kinda short too.  Brock shocks the world by hitting the F5, but Heyman betrays Lesner and KOes the ref, so Big Show can use a chair on Lesner to win the title.  **1/2The Elimination Chamber for the World Title - HHH vs Jericho vs Kane vs Booker T vs RVD vs HBK.  This was a brutal match, beyond belief.  Ppl gettin thrown thru glass, etc.  HBK becomes the man by winning the World Title from HHH!!  *****Extras: 5 Post Interviews, The making of the elimination chamber, a Sunday night heat match, Saliva's "Always" music video.  This DVD is worth every penny.

reviewText: Here's my rundown of the PPV card, keep in mind I rate at a bust of five stars(*****).Six Man Tag Team Elimination Tables Match:Rico & 3 Minute Warning vs. Jeff Hardy & The Dudley Boys****-An amazing opener to start off this pay-per-view! Both teams delivered a fast-paced, entertaining match with amazing spots that will leave you on the edge of your seat! Just when you think you've seen it all in table matches, this match raises the bar even higher.WWE Cruiserweight Championship:Jamie Noble(c) w/ Nidia vs. Billy Kidman****1/2-This was a tremmendous match and while there certainly wasn't much hype to this match, both competitors made this one [heck] of a showdown and could have been a show-stealer if it wasn't for the Elimination Chamber match. Match physcology was used here, making this match almost resemble the fantsastic Benoit/Angle bout at the Rumble in how this match had you on the edge of your seat with incredible spots and scientific wrestling skills.Hardcore Match for the Women's Championship:Trish Stratus(c) vs. Victoria****-The best women's match ever! This bout is better than half the hardcore matches we were treated to on RAW by the likes of Steven Richards and Justin Credible last year. These women let it all hang out here, they gave it everything they had to deliver a great performance. Chairs, irons, kendo sticks, you name it, they used it. This just goes to show how strong the women's division really is.Triple Threat Tag Team Elimination Match for the WWE Tag Team Championship:Edge(c) and Rey Mysterio(c) vs. Los Guerreros vs. Chris Benoit & Kurt Angle****1/2-One of the best Tag Team title matches ever, there were lots of high impact moves, counters, false finishes and high flyng offense from three great tag teams. These guys should have been given more time so they could tell a story in the ring, but all in all, a great bout. Almost outdid Kidman and Noble and would have if they were given some more time.WWE Championship:Brock Lesnar(c) w/ Paul Heyman vs. Big Show***1/2-You can't really rate this match because it was so short. This match didn't even hit the five minute mark when the three count was made. Brock just suplexed Show and destroyed him with the F-5. But keeping up with Survivor Series history, there was a "screwjob". The one getting [messed up], unfortunately, was Brock Lesnar. After Heyman distracted the referee, Big Show got the Chokeslam on Brock for the 1-2-3, and we have a new WWE Champion.Elimination Chamber Match for the World Heavyweight Championship:Triple H(c) vs. Rob Van Dam vs. Booker T vs. Kane vs. Chris Jericho vs. Shawn Michaels*****-Blood was everywhere as these six men destroyed eachother! There was carnage everywhere. The chamber did live up to its hype as this match delivered in so many ways. The brutality was off the charts. The star of the match was without a doubt, ROB Van Dam. He used the cage in so many ways doing all kinds of aerial maneuvers. In the end, "The Heartbreak Kid" walked out victorious and showed the world he still "has it".Bottom Line:This was a great pay-per-view and delivered in a big way.

reviewText: Some argue that this is the greatest PPV of all time, and that may well indeed be a valid point.  Nonetheless, this is a GREAT event, and one that will never be forgotten.  The card features all good matches, except for maybe one.  All in all, this is my personal favorite Survivor Series, and WWE PPV event in general.Here is the card:Tables Match:Bubba Dudley, Spike Dudley, & Jeff Hardy vs. Three Minute Warning & RicoA great great tables match to open the night.  To start off, I really liked the theme of the PPV, and I always enjoy the Madison Square Garden crowd.  This match was very hardcore, and each man in the match put in a lot of effort.  Aside from a couple of botched moments with the tables, this is one of my favorite tables matches of all time.  For big men, Three Minute Warning is an entertaining team, and they work well with the Dudleys and Hardy.  The ending is also great when D-Von returns and reunites with his brothers-- which was a long time coming.  The crowd gets way into the match, and sets a good tone for the rest of the evening.Cruiserweight Title:Jamie Noble w/ Nidia vs. Billy KidmanThese two have put on a lot of good matches in the past, and this one might be their best encounter.  The division for the cruiserweights was at a prime at this point, and it shows here with Kidman and Noble.  I like the duo of Noble and Nidia as well.  Kidman hits a nasty DDT on Noble, which I was surprised to see him kick out of.  The high flying tactics of the match are nice as well.  Kidman takes the belt in a very solid and enjoyable cruiserweight championship match.Women's Title Hardcore Match:Trish Stratus vs. VictoriaThis is perhaps the only time you will see a match such as this one.  The match is a great idea for the women here at Survivor Series.  Victoria's character and abilities are very commendable, and Trish is always great in the ring as well.  There are a lot of weapons used, and there is actually some blood!  Aside from a messed up ending that was quite obvious, the match is a great addition to the hardcore saga.  Victoria takes the strap in the second title swap of the evening.WWE Title:Brock Lesnar w/ Paul Heyman vs. Big ShowThis is the only pitfall for the night.  As I have previously stated, Lesnar brings out the best in the Big Show.  This idea never really gets the chance to be developed in this match.  It is pretty short, and actually kind of dull.  With the proper timing and without the abrupt ending, I believe the match had a lot of potential.  Paul Heyman screws Lesnar out of the title.. go figure.  Yet again we have another title change.WWE Tag Title Elimination Triple Threat:Edge & Rey Meysterio vs. Eddio Guerrero & Chavo Guerrero vs. Kurt Angle & Chris BeniotYou might wonder why this match is after the WWE title match, but after you watch it, you'll know why!  This match is a great technical display by six great athletes.  With all of the talent involved with the match, you should expect nothing less than greatness.  There was also a strange confrontation between Angle and Beniot before the match, which contributed to the chemistry between them during the match.  The match did slow down for a little while due to it being a lengthy contest, but overall a great match at a great PPV!World Title Elimination Chamber Match:Triple H vs. Shawn Michaels vs. Booker T vs. Kane vs. Rob Van Dam vs. Chris JerichoI really liked the WWE's choice to come up with a new match style to main event Survivor Series 2002.  With this comes a lot of risks, all of which paid off on this night!  I liked everything about the contest, from the entry of order, to the pace, to the participants, to the diversity of styles.  There have been a number of chamber matches since the original, none of which I believe to hold a candle to this one.  The original talent was something that made the match a great success that it was.  Triple H and RVD put on a great show as the first two to start the match off.  Each new entering superstar added something new and unique to the match.  It was also very surprising.  I never could guess what would happen next, which is something I am usually able to do during WWE PPVs.  I have watched this match (and this PPV) a number of times.  Highly reccomend. A classic!I was reluctant to give this event five stars, but if you're able to look passed one WWE title match, then I think any WWE fan will agree with me that this was a great event!  Add this DVD to your collection if you have not already done so!

reviewText: WWE Survivor Series 2002 decided to go with quality over quantity, and in doing so the pay per view(ppv) turned out golden, although there was nothing that was completely out of this world, there was tons of great action and basically nothing that was below average. Below is a review of all the matches, the overall extra features and the overall DVD, hopefully it will help you decide if you should buy this DVD or not. The review will not directly give away who wins any of the matches but the winner may seem pretty obvious by my explanations of the matches.( Match Reviews )--- Six Man Table Match - Jeff Hardy and Bubba Ray Dudley and Spike Dudley Vs 3-Minute Warning and Rico ---This was a very good table match, a total of 7 tables broken in this one, some of the table spots where very well done, such as Jeff's Swanton Bomb off a balcony and a huge splash by Jamal off the top rope to the outside. However almost all the other table bumps where just above average or less. The match had a nice pace to it, lots of cool stuff done by Jeff Hardy, this was what I think Jeffs last high risk match before being fired. This match at one point gets edited, on ppv Rico went to the top and stood there for a good 25 seconds before finally being pushed off by Jeff, on this DVD, it makes Rico appear to only be on the ropes for 10 or so seconds. This was most likely edited because during the full version of this mess up u could clearly hear Rico yelling for Jeff to push him off the ropes. Anyways overall a very good table match with a surprise ending aswell, a great way to start off the ppv. (7.5/10)--- WWE Cruiserweight Championship Match - Jamie Noble Vs Billy Kidman ---Good cruiserweight match. It is pretty much the same as there previous matches on Smackdown. Pretty good pace, has some high impact from the top rope and just overall good. (6.5/10)--- Hardcore Women's Championship Match - Trish Stratus Vs Victoria ---For a womens match this was actually pretty good and entertaining, It's pretty obvious that this match was supposed to end with a mirror shot but instead we got a much weaker ending. Good effort, better than most WWE womens matches/ (5.5/10)--- WWE Championship Match - Brock Lesnar Vs Big Show ---This match was a lot better than I thought it was gonna be, not to say it was terrific or anything but still, the moves Big Show took where pretty amazing considering his size, including a belly to belly suplex. Most people could predict the ending and most people will be disappointed with the winner or this match. However good job to both men. (5.5/10)--- Three-Way Elmination Match for the WWE Tag Team Championship - Edge and Rey Mysterio Vs Eddie and Chavo Guerrero Vs Kurt Angle and Chris Benoit ---There was tons of talent in this match, so its easy to get your expectations very high for a match like this, unfortunately it just wasn't that classic lots of people thought it to be, however it still wasn't even close to being called bad. The pace was slower then expected and to a lot of people the first team who gets eliminated will make you mad. There where some very well done spots and all the competitors got most of their signature moves in. I believe the end was just kinda weak but still very good match, just it's hard not to expect better from the competitors in the match. (7.5/10)--- Elimination Chamber Match for the World Heavyweight Championship - Triple H Vs Shawn Michaels Vs Rob Van Dam Vs Kane Vs Chris Jericho Vs Booker T ---I believed this match to be very well done, RVD was great as always and pretty much stole the spotlight for as long as he was in the ring., RVD did a really cool Spiderman type move where he dove off the top rope, clung to the cage and did a 180 Crossbody off it onto Jericho. Shawn Michaels was also good in this match but the only problem was he came out to late, making everything he did just a copy of what had just previously been done. For example, he went threw one of the glass chambers after Jericho already went threw a glass chamber of his own, Or Shawn did a elbow drop off one of the chambers after RVD already did a splash off one of them. Still every competitor did a really good job and you've really got to give all the wrestlers credit for falling on the steal grate which looks like it hurts more then concrete. I believe this to be match of the night. (8.5/10)( Extra Features )There are a fair amount of extra features on this DVD but not when you compare it to Wrestlemania DVD's, the specials that are included are pretty good. There are 5 Interviews done with wrestlers after matches and I must say there great, for the reason that the wrestlers are almost completely out of character and give good comments that to most will be worth listening to. There is also a couple of options that have to do with the elimination chamber, such as the making of the chamber and thoughts on the match by the competitors. A extra match is also included on the DVD, the match is Goldust and The Hurricane Vs Lance Storm and William Regal from Sunday Night Heat that was aired just before this ppv. There is also a great slideshow section of all the Survivor Series Promotion Posters. If u are a Saliva fan then your in for a special surprise as well, cause not only is the "Always" Music video included in the special features but they also play the same song live from WWE The World during the Survivor Series. (7/10)( Overall DVD )I believe this to be a great purchase or at least a rent, the show is very solid threw out, I believe most people will find it hard to complain about the overall show. No match was below 5/10 in my opinion, the special features are pretty good, and included is also the debut of Scott Steiner as he beats on Matt Hardy and Christopher Nowinski, however the part when Steiner asks for the microphone using the "f" word is also edited for the younger audience. Everyone should find at least one thing if not more to like on this DVD. I believe you will want to watch a couple of the matches on this ppv more than once so I say buy it if you've got the money. I hope this review helped you decide on whether or not to buy this DVD.
summary: "buy it if you�ve got the money"

reviewText: <50: Ask for a refund for not only your money, but also your time. [F]50-54: Mediocre & disappointing. [D] (EG: UnForgiven 2002)55-59: Average. [C]60-64: Worth A Watch. [C+] (EG: No Mercy 2002)65-69: Good event that was worth the money. [B]70-74: Very good. [B+]75-79: Make sure you add this ppv to your video or dvd collection. [A] (EG: SummerSlam 2002)80+ : Make sure that the video or dvd is locked in a safe & cannot be erased. Memorable. [A+]I hope that's clear enough. It's almost impossible to score above 85 or below 40 with my PPV Ratings, so that key should help you when reading this review column. I may play around with those comments in the future, but they are pretty self-explanatory as they are.BUBBA-RAY, SPIKE DUDLEY & JEFF HARDY defeated RICO, ROSEY & JAMAL in a Tables Match: Good choice as the hot opener of the night. Sure, this 15 minute spotfest was a little sloppy at times, but the new ingredient of 3 Minute Warning added something extra to the tried & true formula. The match ended when D-Von came out to help Bubba-Ray 3-D Rico through a table for the win. This match contained the loudest berating of a colleague that I have ever heard in the squared circle, when Rico screamed at Jeff to hurry up & get to the ring to take part in a spot. Jeff had just gone through a table off of a balcony. Expect Rico to be punished somehow, very soon. Match Rating...7BILLY KIDMAN defeated JAMIE NOBLE to win the Cruiserweight Title: Solid, if not spectacular, cruiserweight match. This reminded me a lot of last months Noble vs Tajiri bout (except this match was announced to be on the ppv). Hopefully, future c/w title feuds can be built up better than those over the last few months. The false finishes in this bout started a little too early for my liking, but the 2 competitors made the most out of the 8 minutes that were given to them. Match Rating...7VICTORIA defeated TRISH STRATUS in a Hardcore Match to win the Women's Title: I expected a huge effort from these 2 & was not disappointed. The major letdown in this bout was the sudden & uninspiring finish. After 7 minutes of action that was as good as anything that the WWE Hardcore Division gave us in its prime, Victoria won the title with a simple snap suplex. Match Rating...6THE BIG SHOW defeated BROCK LESNAR to win the WWE Championship: Next up was the 4 minute strength test for Brock. Oh, I'm sorry, this was a wrestling match? Could have fooled me!!! Two things really annoyed me about this bout; Firstly, as soon as Heyman said "I'll do anything it takes to see my client win", it became too obvious that he was going to turn on Lesnar. Secondly, The Big Show has just won the most prestigious title in the company, by doing not very much at all. Why not have a 15 minute slugfest where TBS shows great effort to win? Maybe he hasn't got it in him...??? Hard match/segment to rate. I can't pass it, but the intensity was there & Brock proved what he had to. Match Rating...4EDDIE/CHAVO GUERRERO defeated EDGE/REY MYSTERIO & KURT ANGLE/CHRIS BENOIT to win the WWE Tag-Team Titles: I was initially worried that the triple-threat format of this match might not allow these 6 great athletes to show their best. However, the match was predominantly well paced & structured, with the exception of a few hiccups resulting from missed spots. It's really hard to rate these matches nowadays, as all combatants have become a victim of their own high standards. I didn't think this bout was what it could have been, yet it was still very good. Match Rating...8CHRISTOPHER NOWINSKI, MATT HARDY & SCOTT STEINER Segment: Just short of 10 minutes, this segment went for long enough to deserve to be a part of the overall 'PPV Rating'. Achieved its purpose I suppose. Continued Nowinski's & Hardy's heel push, while debuting Steiner without giving away which show he will appear on. It's not what you would call a memorable debut, but it showed what an impact player Big Poppa Pump can be in the WWE, if he remains healthy. Segment Rating...6SHAWN MICHAELS defeated TRIPLE H, CHRIS JERICHO, KANE, BOOKER T & ROB VAN DAM in an Elimination Chamber Match to win the World Heavyweight Title: Got off to a good start when Eric Bischoff clearly explained the rules. Furthermore, choosing RVD as one of the initial entrants was also a good decision, as he was able to do his spots before the match turned into a bloody slugfest. The remainder of the match was very intriguing, and with the exception of Booker T practically playing no part in the proceedings, the elimination's were well timed & the order made sense. Whether HBK or Jericho should have dethroned Triple H will be argued in the weeks to come, but for the purpose of this title match, it didn't really matter. Should the chamber be brought out once a year? I'm not so sure. But it definitely served its purpose for the 2002 version of Survivor Series. Match Rating...8PPV RATING (46/70) = 66Looking at the key (in the 'Appetizers' section), I have basically given Survivor Series a 'B' grade & said that it was 'a good event that was worth the money'. Yep, I'm definitely happy with that rating & comment. An improvement over the last 2 pay-per-view's, Survivor Series was still a fair gap below the best event that the WWE has put on this year. Having only 6 matches can be forgiven due to the hype & format of the Elimination Chamber. Of the 6 matches, 2 were very good, while 3 others were solid. Unfortunately for the third month in a row, the non-main event World Title match let the card down overall. Something must be done about this in the future, as three times in a row is a trend, not a fluke. I understand that there may have been extenuating circumstances due to Brock Lesnar's rib injury, but I have to call it the way I see it. We can only hope that the WWE are on an upward spiral at the moment & the momentum continues for many months to come.

reviewText: This was the PPV that saw the introduction into another WWE creation called "The Elimination Chamber".  Not ever seeing this match or this type of cage before, it was definately something watching.  All the emotion, suprizes, and matches made this one of the greatest WWE PPV's they've done since they split the roster into two shows.Tables Match: Bubba Ray & Spike Dudley, Jeff Hardy vs. 3 Min. Warning & Rico - This was great match full different table spots from various parts of the arena.  The ending with the reunion of Bubba Ray & D-Von was without a doubt the moment of the night with me.Crusierweight Champion Jamie Noble vs Billy Kidman - Above average crusierweight match but didn't do a good job following up the previous match.Hardcore Match: Womens Champion Trish Stratus vs Victoria - It says something when these two had a better hardcore match than a majority of the males wrestlers who've had one.  This looked like a real fight using all these weapons & Victoria in this "psycho bytch" gimmick just makes this match better.WWE Champion Brock Lesnar vs Big Show - This was a match that was more about getting a storyline over than having an actual match.  Brock had a broken rib so he was limited in what he could do but in 4 mins., he did an F-5 to Big Show, had Heyman turn his back on him (which was being set up for weeks) & have Show cheat him out of the WWE Title.Three Way Elimation Match: WWE Tag Team Champions Edge & Rey Mysterio vs Kurt Angle & Chris Benoit vs Los Guerrerros - Without a doubt, match of the year for me.  You haven't seen off the chain tag team wrestling in WWE since this match.  A wrestling clinic put on here by all six men.Elimination Chamber Match: World Heavyweight Champion Triple H vs Shawn Michaels vs Rob Van Dam vs Kane vs Booker T vs Chris Jericho - This match didn't disappoint & honestly, was the best Chamber match to date.  Everyone looked like they legitly could win the belt as one point or another and this match had alot of moments in itself.  Like RVD jumping off the walls like he was SpiderMan and even leaping off the top of one of the cells onto HHH & injuring his throat in the process...and even HHH's performance after that injury is something worth watching.Overall, a perfect addition to anyone's collection.
summary: One Of The Best PPV's Since The Split

reviewText: Jeff Hardy/Buh Buh Ray & Spike Dudley Vs. Three Minute Warning & Rico - Tables MatchVery vicious match! You had the underrated Three Minute Warning and Rico against three veterans of this type of match in Jeff Hardy and two of the Dudleys. I have to say this match had several bump spots but the two that got me out of my chair was seeing one of Three Minute Warning do a splash from the top rope to the outside onto Jeff Hardy who was laying on a table! The other was seeing D-Von from Smackdown (he later returned to RAW) come to help out his "brother" Buh Buh from a three on one situation. Great opener.Jamie Noble Vs. Billy Kidman (WWE Cruiserweight Championship) - Good cruiserweight match. These guys do give it their all nearly everytime they set foot in the ring (they have to really since they don't get the attention as their super-heavyweight "brothers" do). Nice match.Trish Stratus Vs. Victoria (WWE Women's Title/Hardcore Rules) - I have to admit that the women's matches have gotten better over the last couple of years. Not great but definitely have progressed beyond hair pulling. Trish is better than she was when she first started but still seems sloppy at times in the ring. Victoria, on the other hand, is very polished and seems to know what she wants to do.As far as ladies' matches go, this was surprisingly brutal! I know I read one reviewer that said he thought it would be better but if you think about it, how brutal is the WWE going to let a women's match get!? To be honest, I am surprised they let it get as far as it did! Anyway, the match is entertaining if nothing else.The Big Show Vs. Brock Lesner (WWE Title Match) - This match WON'T go down as the best WWE Title match ever but it may go down as one of the most surprising displays of power I have ever seen in a wrestling match! Seeing BS in the F5 manuver of Brock was unbelievable in itself but I am impressed by the way BS sold it! It looks devestating. The only thing that spoiled it was the ending but otherwise it was great.Rey Mysterio/Edge Vs. Chris Benoit/Kurt Angle Vs. Eddie and Chavo Gurrerro (WWE Tag Team Title Match/Three Way Rules) - This was the 2nd best match of the night in my view! A lot of moves, holds, counterholds and even surprise moves (such as Edge getting trapped in BOTH the Crippler Crossface AND the Anklelock)! Entertaining match leading too......Triple H Vs. Shawn Michaels Vs. Booker T. Vs. Rob Van Damn Vs. Chris Jericho Vs. Kane ("RAW" World Title Match/Elimination Chamber) - Going into this bout, we didn't know what to expect. Once is got going, it was basically brutality at its best. While I am not a big HHH fan, I have to give him credit for not only starting the match with RVD but for finishing the contest despite not being able to breathe after RVD's botched 5 Star Frog Splash! Anyway, a great way to cap off a good card!
summary: Decent Card With A Great Main Event!

reviewText: Survivor Series. By rule, it should be the least entertaining major ppv all year. It wasn't. The ppv had no big surprises and it didn't soley rely on big bumps to get it over, a goodthing in today's WWE. He has tortured us for 3 years with bad match after bad match! Oh well, Brock was injured and it was good for business, right?2/5Edge & Rey Mysterio vs. Los Guerreros vs. Benoit & AngleThese six superstars have treated us with some of the bestmatches in five years over the last half-year. Eddie Guerrero continues his endless five star ppv performances. Great spots if a little short.5/5Elimination Chamber:Didn't expect this one to be that good, after all we had no clue what an Elimination Chamber was, and neither did the performers. reviewText: A friend recorded this on PPV and let me borrow it. I watched it and enjoyed it so much that I didn't want to give it back. It was that freakin' good! Ofcourse, I did return it, and now I can't wait to buy it when it comes out on home video. WWE Wrestlemania 18 this year was terrible, but the WWE Survivor Series was the best ever. Bubba Ray Dudley, Spike Dudley, and Jeff Hardy took on Rosie, Jamal, and Rico in an incredible tag team table match. Also, Trish Stratus takes on Victoria in a hardcore match, and both women beat the cr@p out of eachother.Brock Lesnar took on The Bigshow for the WWE Undisputed Championship in a short but cool matchup. I loved the part where Lesnar actually man handles the 500 pound Bigshow! You have to see it to believe it! However, the conclusion of the match is shocking to say the least. The elimination chamber match was very good. Rob Van Dam, Booker T, Kane, Shawn Micheals, Chris Jericho, and Triple H squared off in this awesome main event. The conclusion of the grueling chamber match is very moving and exciting!The bottomline: GET THIS VIDEO WHEN IT COMES OUT! IF YOU'RE A TRUE WRESTLING FAN THEN YOU NEED TO BUY THIS THING! reviewText: Very good effort by the WWE.  It was probably the second best PPV of the year, only behind Summerslam.  This PPV was remembered because it was the first ever Elimination Chamber match, but the undercard was good as well.1. Jeff Hardy, Bubba Ray, & Spike Dudley vs. Rosey, Jamal, & Rico (Table Elimination Match)What a way to kick off the show.  Best opening match of a PPV for the year.  There are many high spots in this match, including Jeff giving Rosey the Swanton off an entrance way and through a table, and Jamal splashing Jeff through a table after jumping off the top turnbuckle and to the arean floor.  D-Von Dudley makes a surprise appearance in the match.  One of the top ten matches of the year in my opinion.  (9.5/10)2. Billy Kidman vs. Jamie Noble (Cruiserweight Title)Good match.  It was probably the worst match of the PPV, but still pretty good.  Nothing too exciting in the match.  (7.5/10)3. Trish Stratus vs. Victoria (Women's Title/Hardcore)Now I am the first one to admit that I do not care for women's wrestling, but this was entertainig.  It was great to see the two use weapons and take some good shots.  Very entertaining match.  (8/10)4. Brock Lesnar vs. Big Show (WWE Title)Short, but good match.  Great spot when Lesnar F-5's Big Show.  Watch the crowd go crazy.  New York City crowds are the best.  Surprising ending.  (8/10)5. Kurt Angle & Chris Benoit vs. Edge & Rey Mysterio vs. Los Guerrero's (Tag Team Title/Triple Threat Elimination Match)Very good tag bout.  It was not as good as the tag title final at No Mercy, but very good nonetheless.  All six men worked great together.  Very innovative moves.  Good match.  (9/10)6. Scott Steiner Makes His DebutSteiner returns to take apart Matt Hardy and Chris Nowinski.  This was probably Steiner's main highlight in the WWE.7. Triple H vs. Shawn Michaels vs. Booker T vs. Chris Jericho vs. Rob Van Dam vs. Kane (World Heavyweight Title/Elimination Chamber)This was Michaels first match since Summerslam.  This was also the debut of the Elimination Chamber.  It was nice that nobody saw it until the PPV started.  Very entertaining match.  RVD did some pretty cool stuff in the match.  Watch Triple H get hit with the Frogsplash on the neck and have to wrestle most of the match unable to breathe.  Good finish with a lot of reversals and close falls.  (9/10)I recommend buying this DVD.  All of the matches are really good.  You will not be disappointed.Overall Rating:  9/10
summary: November 2002 -  Madison Square Garden -  New York, NY

reviewText: WWE Survivor Series 2002 made history when a whole new match was introduced to sports-entertainment fans throughout the world.  Eric Bischoff created the Elimination Chamber match for this event specifically and to decide, among six of Raw's top stars, the World Heavyweight Championship.  Defending champion Triple H had his work cut out for him to say the least.  His five challengers included Rob Van Dam, Booker T, Chris Jericho, Kane and HBK himself, Shawn Michaels.  In other action, Brock Lesnar defends the WWE Championship against the Big Show.  Keep your eyes on Paul Heyman as Brock Lesnar pulls off the most unbelievable show of power in WWE history.  The WWE Tag Team Titles were up for grabs in a triple threat elimination match when Edge and Rey Mysterio defended against Kurt Angle & Chris Benoit and Los Guerreros.  Billy Kidman challenges Jamie Noble for the Cruiserweight Title.  Trish Stratus puts the WWE Women's Title on the line in a hardcore match against Victoria.  In a six man elimination table match, Bubba Ray and Spike Dudley team with Jeff Hardy to take on Three Minute Warning. reviewText: This most recent Survivor Series was notable for several reasons. One, every title that was on the line changed hands. Two, Scott Steiner returned to the WWE for the first time since (I believe) the early 1990's when he was a member of the Steiner Brothers tag team with his brother Rick. Now he is a main event level wrestler and was a heavyweight champion with the WCW. Three, the main event was the debut of the Elimination Chamber (a Hell in a Cell built for 6 men with grating level with the ring).Matches include a 6 man (tag) table match (RAW) that was somewhat boring with the exception of a couple of high spots performed by Jeff Hardy. The cruiserweight championship match (Smackdown) between Jamie Noble and Billy Kidman was perhaps the best singles match of the night. It featured some impressive moves that we haven't seen in a while (a strong DDT from the top rope) and was fast paced and entertaining. The women's championship hardcore match (RAW) between Victoria and Trish Stratus was notable only for the amount of physical abuse the women were willing to put themselves through to entertain. The women's division has really been stepping up lately, but the match still wasn't that special. It established the intensity of newcomer Victoria's character a bit more, but that's about it. The Triple Threat Elimination Tag Team Championship match (Smackdown) was perhaps the Match of the Night. The teams were Kurt Angle/Chris Benoit vs Eddie Guererro/Chavo Guererro vs Edge/Rey Mysterio. The WWE Championship Match (Smackdown) between Brock Lesnar and the Big Show was happily short, but showed off the strength of Lesnar."Big Poppa Pump" Scott Steiner debuted by interrupting a promo cut by Matt Hardy and Christopher Nowinski. Steiner tossed Hardy and Nowinski around, spouted off a couple of catch-phrases and left the ring. I wasn't impressed.The main event was the first ever Elimination Chamber match and was for the World Heavyweight Championship (RAW). The pace was fairly slow, and for a main event level match with the hype of the Elimination Chamber, it wasn't very impressive of a match. I appreciate the abuse the wrestlers (Triple H, Shawn Michaels, Kane, Rob Van Dam, Chris Jericho, Booker T) put their bodies through to entertain us while risking serious injury with all the steel of the cage, but the match wasn't that good. It was impressive knowing that Triple H nearly had his throat crushed by RVD and could barely breathe for most of the match (and he still competed, though spending a lot of time in the middle of the match laying on the side). HBK (Shawn Michaels) was a non-factor for most of the match and only really got into it near the end. While I am a long time wrestling fan and remember Michaels when he first joined the WWF, and I feel nostalgic watching HBK compete again, the match didn't live up the billing.Overall, this was an above average Pay Per View, but not stellar.

reviewText: The 6 man tag team elimination tables match was a good hard-hitting reminder of the 1990's ECW. The Cruiserweight title match was a solid/high-flying bout. reviewText: The fans of New York City were treated to a night of legendary beginnings as this Survivor Series saw the debut of one of the most dangerous matches in WWE history! The Elimination Chamber! You thought Hell in a Cell was big?? The psychotic and unpredictable mind of Eric Bischoff came up with the idea of this match. The structure itself is 16 ft (4.9 m) high, 36 ft (11 m) in diameter, weighs over 10 short tons (9,100 kg), and comprises 2 mi (3.2 km) and 6 short tons (5,400 kg) of chain. Not one match on here is boring! They all move at a fairly fast pace and keep you on the edge of your seat throughout. This is the 2002 Survivor Series!1.) 6 Man Tag Team Elimination Tables Match: Jeff Hardy, Bubba Ray Dudley, and Spike Dudley vs 3 Minute Warning- A great opener to start off Survivor Series! The last time Jeff and Bubba were in a Tables match in NYC, they were beating the heck out of each other at the Royal Rumble 2000 and now they're teaming up and along with Spike! This match saw table spots from different parts of the arena and ends with D-Von (who was on the Smackdown brand at the time) interfering and helping Bubba win the match, signaling a Dudley Boyz reunion  Match rating: 10/10Segment: The beautiful Stacy Keibler is live at The World and introduces Saliva who sing the Survivor Series theme, Always.2.) Cruiserweight Championship Match: Billy Kidman vs Jamie Noble w/Nidia (c)- This was a fast paced match and a good Cruiserweight match but wasn't as exciting as their past matches. Nidia interfered in many parts of the match, including slapping Kidman across the face. Noble went after Kidman, but missed, and knocked Nidia off the apron. Kidman managed to hit the Shooting star press for the win and become the new Cruiserweight Champion  Match rating: 7/103.) Hardcore Women's Championship Match: Victoria vs Trish Stratus (c)- The feud between Victoria and Trish had gotten pretty brutal or in the words of J.R "bowling shoe ugly" leading up to Survivor Series and it all came to a head in this match. Many different weapons get put into play in this match, from a broom stick to an ironing board to a cookie sheet and so much more! At one point a mirror was supposed to be used in the match but Trish accidentally stepped on it so it never got used. The ending comes when Victoria (with a bloody nose) sprays Trish in the eyes with a fire extinguisher and suplexes her to win the match and her first ever Women's Championship. This match was brutal in ways and there's proof of it as in the extras of the DVD, Victoria talks about a bump she got on her forehead from Trish during the match.  Match rating: 8/104.) WWE Championship Match: Big Show vs Brock Lesnar w/Paul Heyman (c)- Lesnar walked out for this match with injured ribs which were injured when Big Show (who had been traded from Raw to Smackdown) attacked him at the entrance ramp and threw him off the stage. After that point, Heyman believed that Lesnar could not beat nor F5 the Big Show but Lesnar did not listen and ended up leading to this match. This match is about less than 5 minutes and starts off with Show taking advantage of Brock's injured ribs early on in the match but Lesnar comes back at him and does the unthinkable and hits the F5 on the Big Show getting perhaps the biggest pop of the night. Right as he gets ready to pin and put away the Big Show, Paul Heyman pulls the referee out of the ring and clocks him, turning on Brock. What follows is Brock chasing Heyman around the ring before Big Show nails Brock with the chair and chokeslams him on it to get the win and the WWE Championship. The camera follow Paul Heyman and his new client to the parking lot and watch them enter a limo and get the hell out of dodge  Match rating: 7/105.) Triple Threat Elimination Tag Team Championship Match: Kurt Angle and Chris Benoit vs Los Guerreros vs Edge and Rey Mysterio (c)- I really enjoyed this match as these 3 had been involved in a feud with each other in some sort of way over the last month or two prior to this PPV. What you get here is an awesome, technical match put on by 6 of the greatest superstars to ever step in a ring. This match goes back and forth as move sets range from high flying to submissionist to technical. The quickness of the match slows down a bit after the first team, which happen to be Angle and Benoit get eliminated but it's still a great match and not one to be taken for granted6.) Elimination Chamber World Heavyweight Championship Match: Chris Jericho vs Booker T vs Kane vs Shawn Michaels vs RVD vs Triple H (c)- In the first ever Elimination Chamber match, this saw Raw's top 6 superstars go through hell to make sure they were the one that left Madison Square Garden as the World Heavweight Champion. The first two to start off the match were RVD and the champ Triple H. From there on out, this match is absolutely tremendous and exciting to watch as the superstars use practically every part of the Chamber to their advantage as a weapon on their opponents. The match gets brutal real quick as Triple H is busted open within the first 10 minutes of the match. A little bit of blood is spilled throughout the match from HHH, Jericho, and Michaels. The match ends on a high note bringing this awesome PPV to an awesome end!DVD Extras:- Saliva's Always Music Video- Eric Bischoff in New York- A look at the Elimination Chamber in which the Chamber is shown being constructed- Lance Storm and William Regal vs The Hurricane and Goldust from Sunday Night Heat- Interviews from Rico, Victoria, the Guerreros, Booker T, and RVD- Looking back at the Elimination Chamber. Superstars from the match give their opinions and thoughts on the match- Photo Gallery of all the promotional Survivor Series posters
summary: One of the Best Survivor Series PPVs of the Ruthless Aggression Era!

reviewText: I have been a wrestling fan since 1996 and have watched all kinds of wrestling. I have a wrestling DVD/VHS collection spanning over 50 all together. This is the most complete and accurate review of this event you will find. I hope you find this review helpful; remember to vote helpful or not helpful. (Note-Each DVD I review has a "Match of the DVD" award somewhere in it.)WWE Survivor Series 2002This event is my favorite event of all-time. Everything on the card was excellent. 5 titles were on the line on this card. I love the staging and color scheme used for the event. The crowd seems very energetic all night and it really helped the card. Everyone seemed to play an equal part on making the entire event remarkable. I recommend this to anyone who loves wrestling.Six-Man Table MatchJeff Hardy, Bubba Ray Dudley, & Spike Dudley VS 3-Minute Warning & RicoWhat an amazing way to start off this event. This match is fast paced and at some points, very brutal. There is a lot of highflying including one of Jeff Hardy's sickest moves to date. The ending is very surprising as well.RATING- 9.5/10Between these two matches, Saliva performs "Always" live at The World.WWE Cruiserweight ChampionshipJamie Noble(c) w/Nidia VS Billy KidmanThe Smackdown side of the show begins with a bang in this match. There are lots of high impact and highflying moves in this match. Jamie Noble hits one of the sickest DDT's I've seen in my life. The action doesn't seem to slow down at all.RATING- 8.5/10Women's Championship- Hardcore MatchTrish Stratus(c) VS VictoriaThis is the first Hardcore match for the Women's Championship in a long time. If you want to see the first Hardcore Women's Title match, check outWWE Hardcore. Usually in a Women's match you don't expect much, but this match was excellent. There were a lot of weapons used and good action. King and J.R. offer up some funny commentary during this match as well.RATING- 8/10WWE ChampionshipBrock Lesnar(c) w/Paul Heyman VS Big ShowBrock Lesnar has been champion since Summerslam of that year. He has beaten opponents like The Rock and The Undertaker. Three Questions and a Statement made this match extremely great and told the story very well. The three questions were: "Can Lesnar suplex the Big Show?", "Can Lesnar F-5 the Big Show", and "Can Lesnar beat the Big Show". That sets up the story which Lesnar is going to be telling in this match. Also, Paul Heyman says a statement before the match that foreshadows an event that will happen in the match. That statement is "I'll do anything to make sure that my client walks out with the WWE Championship". It was an awesome match. Sure, it was short but it told the story perfectly. They had a longer match atWWE Royal Rumble 2003, and it wasn't good at all.RATING- 9/10WWE Tag Team Championships-Triple Threat EliminationEdge & Mysterio(c) VS Kurt Angle & Chris Benoit VS Los GuerrerosThis match had an interesting dynamic between Angle and Benoit. Angle and Benoit aren't on the same page at a lot of times, but when they are they can tear through there opponents. There is a lot of action in this match, but after the first elimination the crowd seems to not care anymore.RATING- 8.5/10Between these two matches, Chris Nowinski and Matt Hardy cut a promo on how New Yorkers are loopid (losers and stupid). This all seems like a big waste of time until a debuting Scott Steiner returns and destroys both of them. J.R.'s commentary on the affair is funny as ever.World Heavyweight Championship- Elimination Chamber (Match of the DVD)Triple H(c) VS Chris Jericho VS Kane VS Booker T VS Rob Van Dam VS Shawn MichaelsIf you do not understand how an Elimination Chamber works, it's not that complicated. Two men start. Every 5 minutes an internal chamber will open and release 1 of 4 superstars randomly. The match is elimination, so whoever is last remaining is the winner. Now, this match is incredible. No other Elimination has reached the bar that this one set. There are a lot of internal feuds between people within the chamber. A lot of blood is shed in this match. There are some absolutely amazing, and absolutely brutal, spots. Also, on a side note, Chris Jericho's music is performed by Saliva. They are playing "King of my World", which is an awesome song.RATING- 10/10

reviewText: I think of Survivor Series from 2002 as one of my all-time favorite pay-per-views the WWE has ever put on (or at least while they've been under the 'WWE' name). The atmosphere in Madison Square Garden was completely electric, and it goes to show why WWE holds shows so frequently there. Anything I say in the next couple paragraphs will all be from memory, since I don't have the time to sit down and rewatch the event.The main event was the first of its kind, I remember. It definitely lived up to the hype, and all the guys put on a heck of an outing. It was the first time Shawn Michaels was crowned world champion in four years, and I remember completely marking out when he got the three count. The brutality of this match is a bit exaggerated, but it's definitely the high point of the show.The undercard had its share of bright spots too, and really, aside from the Lesnar/Big Show match, nothing stands out as being anything but good. The opening table match was neat, and one of the last Matt and Jeff Hardy had the honor of participating in. This was at the point when Jeff was about to leave the WWE. This table match pales in comparison to the same one the team had with the Dudleys at Royal Rumble 2000, but it's still fun.The cruiserweight title match was interesting as well. I remember somewhere in the midst of the fight someone takes a vicious DDT off the turnbuckle, which is probably one of the coolest and most vicious moves you'll see on this DVD. The triple team tag match is good, but doesn't stand up to the match two of the teams shared a month before at No Mercy. Either way the match here is good, and there are some really neat spots with Angle and Benoit. I love those guys!In the end, Survivor Series is definitely worth a buy. It has some new matches never before seen (even though most of them were expanded on at a later date), everyone was on top of their game on this night, and the arena of MSG was on fire. Check it out.9/10
summary: Best Survivor Series Ever? Oh yeah.

reviewText: Hello and welcome to my review on Survivor Series 2002. I use a grading system and each match receives a grade. Then to determine how the show ranks the total of the matches scores are divided by the number of matches giving the grade and a comment about whether you should buy it or not. The grading system is as follows.Grading E- = 0 - 8.33%-Waste of time and money.E  = 8.33 - 16.66%-Waste of time and money.E+ = 16.66 - 24.99%-Waste of time and money.D- = 24.99 - 33.32%-Very poor event maybe read about it.D  = 33.32 - 41.65%-Poor event with a little something standing out.D+ = 41.65 - 50%-Not a very good event but it just below passing.C- = 50 - 55.55%-Just below average worth a watch.C  = 55.55 - 61%-An average event worth a renting.C+ = 61 - 66.65%-Above average worth a purchase if you can find it for cheap.B- = 66.65 - 72.20%-Good event with a lot of good stuff. Purchase if you're a collector or interested.B  = 72.20 - 77.75%-Good quality event which is worth purchase and should be collected.B+ = 77.75 - 83.30%-Very high quality event with awesome matches. Must have for anyone.A- = 83.30 - 88.85%-Excellent event, must have for anyone. Lock this one away.A  = 88.85 - 94.40%-Extremely spectacular event with lots of great stuff. Lock this away.A+ = 94.40 - 100%-DVD of the century, must buy and keep in a very safe place.Match One-Elimination Table Match-Spike Dudley,Buh Buh Ray Dudley & Jeff Hardy Vs Rosey,Jamal & Rico-This was fairly good and it was a good solid choice for the opener. They did some of the old moves from some of the past table matches. Rico and his team are still not that great in the ring except in this match they did alright. An absolute spectacular ending with one of the great moments noone would expect. My rating 8.71/10.Match Two-Cruiserweight Championship-Jamie Noble(C)Vs Billy Kidman-This was a fairly good cruiserweight match with some good spots and action in it. Too bad we don't still have some of the better cruiserweights such as these two,Akio,Shannon Moore,X-Pac and many others. The ending of this was great and hopefully these two have a rematch or a long extended feud which would be great. My rating 8.81/10.Match Three-Hardcore Match-Womens Championship-Trish Stratus(C)Vs Victoria-This was a good solid hardcore match between these two ladies with quite a few weapons used with some good spots done. The ending wasn't the greatest but after what these two went through it was acceptable. My rating 7.51/10.Match Four-WWE Championship-Brock Lesnar(C)Vs Big Show-This was a great show of strength by these two men. It was a fairly short match probably because of Brocks rib injury which was worked on quite a bit. There was two ref bumps which were suited for this match as it fit the whole concept of this match. This was a solid match but hopefully they don't have two many more matches as the longer the match the more slow and boring it would get, but this match was very well done. My rating 9.28/10.Match Five-Triple Threat Elimination Tag Match-WWE Tag Team Championship-Rey Mysterio & Edge(C)Vs Eddie Guerrero & Chavo Guerrero Vs Kurt Angle & Chris Benoit-This was a great match with all the teams doing what they do best. Eddie & Chavo were playing the cheating heels, Kurt and Benoit were arguing like a married couple as always and Rey & Edge had the crowd cheering for them non stop. This was a match with great action,spots,bumps and a great time for it. My rating 9.51/10.Match Six-Main Event-Elimination Chamber-World Heavyweight Championship-HHH(C)Vs RVD Vs "Y2J"Chris Jericho Vs Booker T Vs Kane Vs "HBK"Shawn Michaels-This was off the charts with non stop action for about forty minutes! Half of the wrestlers bled and there was no cheap eliminations and it was plain brutal with lots of spots,bumps and a real injury caused to HHH by RVD doing a super high flying move. The whole match was great and the ending was super amazing as well and it just capped off this great show. My rating 9.86/10.Overall Survivor Series scored very well as it got 53.68 out of 60. It is 89.46% and that is exceptionally good. Overall in a grade this show received an A. It was an extremely spectacular event with lots of great stuff, lock this show away forever and make sure noone gets it away from you. The WWE Tag Titles,WWE Championship and the Elimination Chamber were exceptional and off the charts. This was a great show and a great DVD.

reviewText: This my friends w/o a shadow of a doubt is THE Best Survivor Series EVER!I mean you had 6 AWESOME matchesBubby Ray/Spike/Jeff Hardy vs. 3 Minute Warning & Rico-The 6 Man Elimination Tables Matchan awesome match, Jeff Hardy did a swanton off the top of the entrance, and the Dudleys reuniting, a great way to start the show. AWESOME MATCH!Jamie Noble w/Nidia vs. Billy Kidman-WWE Cruiserweight Championship-Awesome Match from both men.Trish Stratus vs. Victoria-Hardcore Match for the WWE Women's World ChampionshipAnother Awesome Match, the best Women's Hardcore Match I've ever seen from both Trish and Victoria, this one INDED raised the bar in the Women's Division. AWESOME MATCH!Brock Lesnar vs. Big Show-WWE ChampionshipBrock Lesnar hitting Big Show w/the Belly to Belly Suplex was AWESOME! Great performance by both men.Edge/Mysterio vs. Angle/Benoit vs. Los Guerreros-Triple Threat Elimination Match for the SD! WWE Tag Team Championship (The old WCW World Tag Team Championship)Awesome Match including some high flying action. ANOTHER AWESOME MATCH!The return of Big Poppa Pump Scott Steiner cleaning house on Chris Nowitski and Matt Hardy. AWESOME!The Elimination Chamber (A combination of Hell in a Cell, Royal Rumble, and NWA/WCW's Wargames rolled up into 1 AWESOME Match) for the World Heavyweight Championship (The old NWA/WCW Big Gold World Heavyweight Championship)The Best Chamber Match in WWE History, RVD doing a Spider-Man/Matrix Move was COOL! RVD doing the 5* Frog Splash on Triple H from the top of the Chamber was AWESOME!HBK also doing the flying elbow off the top of one of those internal chambers was AWESOME as well and he wins the World Title Gold for a 4th Time and becomes a Golden Five Club Winner in the WWE. AWESOME MATCH!Extras:Interviews from Rico, Victoria, Los Guerreros, Booker T., and RVDPlus a Bonus Match from HEAT prior to Survivor Series Goldust/Hurricane vs. Regal/StormMaking of the Elimination Chamber, Looking Back @ the Elimination Chamber, and Eric Bischoff @ Madison Square GardenPlus the Saliva Music Video as well as the Poster GalleryThis my friends is a must buy for all of you fans of Survivor Series and trust me, you are going to LOVE it.2002 Survivor Series DVD & Wrestlemania XIX DVD are the 2 Big Events that you must see and have on DVD.THEY ARE AWESOME!Also the very first Elimination Chamber Match is MUCH better than the ones @ Summerslam 2003, New Year's Revolution 2005 & 2006.and if you're also looking for more Wargames Type Matches, then I also recommend that you also buy TNA Lockdown 2005 and TNA Lockdown 2006, THEY ARE AWESOME!

reviewText: This was the very first Survivor Series that I bought, and I believe that I did not waste a single cent of my money. Each match was at least a 7/10 or higher. The crowd was really great that night and it really helped in some of the matches. Every single title changed hands and a lot of new rivalries started.The six man table elimination match was the best opener to any ppv I have seen in a while. I couldn't keep track of how many tables were destroyed, but a lot were. Jeff Hardy was the highlight of this match, he did a lot of high moves. And the ending was great when the Dudley Boyz reunited and gave the 3D to Rico through a table. 8.5/10The women's title match was a big surprise, both women work well together and the no holds barred stipulation really helped it. I like Victoria a lot better than I did back then. 7.5/10The crusierweight championship was good for that sick DDT Kidman gave Noble at the end of the match. I didn't know just how good Nidia looks in shorts until that moment when she got in the ring. A good match between the two. 7.5/10The WWE championship was the only letdown of the night. They had to make it short because of the wwe tag team match and the main event. But only 5 minutes? Thats a little too short in my opinion. Still amazing how Brock managed to lift the Big Show up like that. Paul Heyman turns on Brock which was a big surprise, and Brock finally becomes a good guy. Still it was a little too obvious after all the weeks of how Heyman kept saying Brock couldn't beat the Big Show. 7/10The Smackdown tag team titles match was the second best match of the night. All six men were great in this match. I wish the guereroes would get back together. Scary moment when Rey slipped after trying to jump on top of the ring ropes. This was the start of the Kurt, Benoit rivarly till the Royal Rumble. A good match all the way through. 8.5/10The elimination chamber match was the best match of the night by far, and the best match out of all the survivor series matches in history. Triple H went the entire length of the match, even with a busted throat, and still almost manages to win. Chris Jericho was great and really got pounded into the side of the mini cell by Kane. RVD was great also and really used the cage well, it was too bad though that they way he was eliminated was by the frog splash. Shawn wins after being away for more than five years and becomes world heavyweight champion. This was a great match. 11/10Survivor Series is the best one out of the past survivor series, and will become a classic night to remember. Every single match is worth the money, so buy this now.
